[SN]TITLE[SN]
Conwy man faces trial over FaceTime 'harassment hanging'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man is to stand trial accused of harassing his partner by pretending to hang himself on FaceTime.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Stephen Moore, 44, of Conwy, denied harassment by making four calls on his iPad with the last one showing him with a rope around his neck in an attic.
Prosecutor Justin Espie told Llandudno magistrates' court he began screaming and the woman had alerted police.
A district judge freed Moore from custody on conditional bail until his trial on 16 May.
